FBIS4-13783 "drnes079_g_94002" FBIS-NES-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 Sudan Armed Forces Spokesman on Israeli Arms Supply to SPLA Armed Forces Spokesman on Israeli Arms Supply to SPLA EA2304175694 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network in Arabic 1300 GMT 23 Apr 94 EA2304175694 Omdurman Republic of Sudan Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Staff Lieutenant Colonel Muhammad Bashir Sulayman, the official spokesman of the Armed Forces, issued a statement today in which he referred to reports appearing in Western media about Israeli military support for the Sudan People's Liberation Army [SPLA] rebel movement and the visit of rebel John Garang to Israel in search of military and political support. The statement stressed that the military support for the two camps of the rebel movement was not new and that Israel has been one of the principal sources of supply to the rebel movement since the latter was founded.
